<div>Dear all, Just wanted to warn people of kundalini synd=
rome based on my recent experience of a patient of mine. I am doing a psych=
iatry job at present, and have been involved in the care of someone who see=
ms to think she has had a spontaneous awakening of their kundalini since ch=
ildhood. This has involved out-of-body experiences and surges of energy in =
the body. She is not of Indian origin and had never heard of kundalini unti=
l her symptoms started and she searched for an explanation. We have not bee=
n able to find anything physically wrong with her (all tests normal)- so it=
 might be that this is due to deranged kundalini. Many people we call menta=
lly ill describe themselves as having a spiritual crisis, or unwanted spont=
aneous kundalini awakening- this has triggered interest and research into t=
his topic in mainstream psychiatry. Unfortunately these patients are not we=
ll-understood by western medicine, and as we have no treatments for derange=
d
 kundalini, we struggle to help them. Many yogis try to forcibly waken th=
e kundalini. My experience with this lady confirmed my feeling that kundali=
ni should not be forcibly wakened. This woman wants to kill herself at time=
s because the suffering from the deranged energy is so bad. She feels it wi=
ll consume her, and it is something she cannot escape from. I wondered what=
 solution there could be to her problem. The logical one was to pray to the=
 Divine Mother, who manifests as the kundalini to relieve the suffering of =
this woman- and either cure her, or give her the strength to bear this. May=
 I request that the good samaritans among you pray for her, and for others =
like her (whom we may not know of)- their suffering really is pitiable. And=
 let us be careful in our sadhana so as not to end up in this situation our=
selves. Perhaps this is why the bhakti marga is the safest. It is perhaps s=
afest to say "let me be your instrument" and leave the kundalini
 rising bi=
t to God's will. Om Dum Durgayai Namaha Aparna </div></div></div></div></di=
